cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the performance of mobile ad-hoc networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses tools from stochastic geometry to derive closed form expressions, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with the Random Waypoint Mobility Model, which is a type of simulation, indicating a possible fit with cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of interference on network performance, which is a topic related to signal processing, suggesting a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
